SECTION 2: LITERARY AND SCHOLARLY WORKS
================================================================================

Librandi's written output, while not voluminous, was significant in the fields
of Albanian linguistics and late 19th-century Italian literature.

WORK 1: "AI CADUTI D'AFRICA" (1896)
-----------------------------------
Publication Year:  1896
Publication Place: Cremona
Genre:             Poetry/Literary work

In 1896, while in Cremona (Lombardy), Librandi published his second book,
titled "Ai caduti d'Africa" (To the Fallen of Africa). This work appeared
during the era of Italian colonial expansion in Africa. Italy had begun its
 colonial ventures in Eritrea and Somalia, and the Italian army had suffered
a humiliating defeat at the Battle of Adwa in Ethiopia in 1896.

The title suggests the work was an elegiac or commemorative piece honoring
Italian soldiers who died in African campaigns. Works of this nature were
common in the patriotic-nationalist literature of the period.

WORK 2: "GRAMMATICA ALBANESE CON LE POESIE RARE DI VARIBOBA" (1897)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Publication Year:  1897
Publisher:         Ulrico Hoepli, Milan
Full Title:        "Grammatica Albanese con le poesie rare del reverendo poeta
                   Giulio Variboba di Mbusati"
Genre:             Linguistics/Grammar/Anthology
Significance:      FIRST EDITION of an Albanian grammar in Italian

This is Librandi's magnum opus and his most celebrated work. Published by
the prestigious Hoepli publishing house in Milan in 1897, this volume
represents a landmark in Albanian linguistic studies.

CONTENTS OF THE GRAMMAR:
------------------------
1. Albanian Grammar Section - A comprehensive guide to the Albanian
   language, structured for Italian speakers. The grammar covered:
   - Phonology and pronunciation
   - Morphology (nouns, verbs, adjectives, etc.)
   - Syntax and sentence structure
   - Vocabulary and common expressions

2. Poetry Section - The volume includes rare poems by Giulio (Jul) Variboba,
   a revered poet from Mbusati (Macchia Albanese), another Arbëreshë
   community in Calabria.

GIULIO VARIBOBA (1725-1788):
-----------------------------
Giulio Variboba was an 18th-century Albanian poet from San Giorgio Albanese
(Mbusati in Arbëreshë), in the province of Cosenza. He is considered one of
the most important early writers in the Albanian language. His works were
written in the Tosk dialect using the Latin alphabet, making them significant
for both literary and linguistic studies.

Variboba's poetry dealt with religious themes, moral teachings, and the
condition of the Arbëreshë communities. By the late 19th century, his works
had become rare, and Librandi's edition helped preserve and disseminate them.

HISTORICAL SIGNIFICANCE:
------------------------
- This was the first edition of an Albanian grammar published in Italian
- It helped establish scholarly study of the Albanian language in Italy
- The inclusion of Variboba's poetry helped preserve Arbëreshë literary heritage
- The work contributed to the broader 19th-century interest in linguistics,
  dialectology, and minority languages in Italy

AVAILABILITY TODAY:
-------------------
The work has entered the public domain and is available through:
- Internet Archive (archive.org) - full digital text
- Various antiquarian booksellers
- Modern facsimile reprints

